I received poor treatment as a customer at Butterfly Sushi. I left my phone number with the hostess when entering my name for a table, which she gladly accepted and wrote next to my name. Hours later, after waiting outside in the cold, I entered the restaurant to check the status of my table. I was shocked to see that my name had been crossed off the list. I raised this concern with the hostess, who told me that I was removed because I did not answer my phone when they called. I did not receive a phone call. I displayed my call log to the hostess to demonstrate this. Upon seeing this, she apologized and told me that she would arrange for the next available table. My party and I left the restaurant (we ate at Tsukiji Fish Market, 1156 W. Grand Ave, and had a delightful experience there). While dining at Tsukiji Fish Market, I received a phone call from Butterfly Sushi, notifying me that my table was ready, proving that my number was available to the hostess all along.

"My family and I were in Chicago, just West of Greek Town for a music recital and I decided to do a quick search on Google Maps for a place to eat. We weren't sure what we were in the mood for which made it tough since there were literally hundreds of restaurants within a mile or so. There were Greek and Italian restaurants everywhere, but one standout caught our eye, Butterfly Sushi. It had a great rating with hundreds of reviews and was nearby, so we gave it a shot. Were we glad we did!  Parking wasn't too bad. We found a spot about a block away (great for Chicago) and since it was Sunday, there was no need to feed the meter. When we entered the restaurant we were warmly greeted by the hostess and quickly brought to our table. My wife went to use the restroom (no complaints there either) and I noticed a gentleman at the adjoining table talking VERY loudly. When I asked the waitress if we could move one table over, she accommodated us without hesitation. After that first hiccup (no fault of the restaurant), the rest of the evening was excellent! The waitress promptly took our order after asking a few questions, and brought our drinks quickly.  I ordered the Chicken Katsu, my wife ordered the Crunchy Spicy Tuna Maki-Mono, and my daughter ordered the Chicken Teriyaki. Their Miso Soup was typical, but tasty, but the stars were the entrees. We all enjoyed our meal. The Chicken Katsu was excellent, cooked to perfection and flavorful. My wife's sushi impressed her, and my daughter's Chicken Teriyaki was equally impressive.  Our bill came quickly, the prices were reasonable and accurate, and we were on our way within an hour of entering. I HIGHLY recommend Butterfly Sushi if you're in the mood for Asian food in an upscale, service-oriented environment!"
